Armedeus....  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uznailvh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Znail vh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br>  Posts: 220<br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/22/02 4:05 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bertoxx gnome wizzies... can't buy a thing!!</span><hr size=1> You are KOS to guards? Strange, I think agnostic gnomes arent and I asumed Bertox would be better not worse.<br>
<br>
Anyway, if you cant find any place you are welcome, then its time to see if you can imorove faction somewhere perhaps.<br>
<br>
Oh, do you have Luclin? There are cities there as well where spells are sold and at least one of them should like you. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utimmahp.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Timmah P</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br>  Posts: 187<br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/23/02 6:41 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bertoxx gnome wizzies... can't buy a thing!!</span><hr size=1> did you go into the mines under Ak'anon?   The good and neutral gnome int casters can buy spells in the easy to find building at the top of the ramp leading up a rock cliff.  The evil gnomes have to run deep into the city and find an opening into the mines, then trample around down there until you get lucky enough to stumble on to your spell merchants / trainers. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utehutibloodstorm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tehuti Bloodstorm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 972<br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/24/02 10:09 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bertoxx gnome wizzies... can't buy a thing!!</span><hr size=1> The problem with Bertox wizards, whether human or gnome, is that their guild leaders are placed with the necro's. Who conveniantly have their own spell merchants, yet wizards/chanters/mages do not.<br>
<br>
<br>
I would normally recommend the Red Wine for Neriak, yet the new trade in and invis would not work as you are KoS there.<br>
<br>
The best bet, is to go to Tox and AE the Warrens. Also camp the necro at the docks, saving all the bones he drops. Turn these bones into the magician guild leader. Killing the necro should raise the Crimson Hands faction, which is the wizard faction of Erudin.<br>
<br>
Also, two things to note of erudin. It is impossible to raise Quellious faction, as you need amiable or better to do their quests. That being said, the paladins near the portal gems are not your friends. <br>
<br>
Deepwater knights are easy to raise, I am ally as a DE. Actually done some of their quests, the barnacle BP is a nice newbie toy. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
If you do treant killing, there is one bard also by the gem leading into the erudin palace, so you may want to invis up before going to the palace.<br>
<br>
Do NOT go to the second floor of the chanter guild (the yellow one) without invisibility. There is a HE chanter named Parlone who will charm you, then proceed to wipe you out. I was charmed for 15 minutes, the funny thing was apparently as a DE NPC I was on default faction so was killing all the newbie erudites for awhile. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  They all thought I was some new quest mob. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Perhaps Katta might be your answer, it's just rough as a Bertox caster. Though the Qeynos Bertox Temple is one of the coolest placest in old world EQ. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><img src= "http://khaemwese.homestead.com/files/T2.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showPrevMessage?topicID=750.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showNextMessage?topicID=750.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.emailToFriend?topicID=750.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.threadControl?topicID=750.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=750.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=750.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=htt